Slide 1 — Title

Good morning everyone. Today I’ll be presenting my summer internship project, AutoLake: Agentic Data Product Generation.

The goal of this project is to automate a manual data engineering workflow where semi-structured data in the Lakehouse is transformed into normalized, analytics-ready Lakehouse Data Products.

At a high level, AutoLake takes schema information, existing Lakehouse metadata, and business use cases as input, and then uses an agent-driven workflow to generate normalized structures, Pure code, MatViews, and Lakehouse Data Product artifacts.

The main idea is simple: we already have valuable business data in the Lakehouse, but it is not directly usable because it lands in a semi-structured format. AutoLake helps convert that raw data into trusted, reusable, queryable data products.

